    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="letter">
                <pb n="1" facs="Edgeworth_NLS_42180_1835_06_14_page01.jpg"/>
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Edgeworthstown_IE"/><choice><orig>Edgeworth town</orig><reg>Edgeworthstown</reg></choice>
                        <date when="1835-06-14">June 14<hi rend="superscript">h</hi> 1835</date>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>
                        <choice><orig>D<hi rend="superscript">r</hi></orig><reg>Dear</reg></choice> Sir<lb/>
                    </salute>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    You may recollect that it was<lb/>
                    I who had the honor of <choice><orig>re=<lb/>
                    commending</orig><reg>recommending</reg></choice> it to you to<lb/>
                    deal with the author of<lb/>
                    <title ref="./Workography.xml#Berth1"><hi rend="underline">Bertha</hi></title> though I had not<lb/>
                    seen the manuscript but<lb/>
                    judged only from my general<lb/>
                    knowledge of the abilities of<lb/>
                    the author &amp; from a former<lb/>
                    work - I believe you have<lb/>
                    been satisfied with the result<lb/>
                    and upon the strength of this<lb/>
                    I now venture another <choice><orig>recom<lb/>
                    mendation</orig><reg>recommendation</reg></choice> to you of a lady<lb/>
                    who is personally a stranger<lb/>
                    to me but who is known to<lb/>
                    me and perhaps to you by<lb/>
                    her work, <persName ref="./Personography.xml#CarmA1">M<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi> Carmichael</persName> -<lb/>
                    author of <title ref="./Workography.xml#Domes1">"Domestic Manners<lb/>
                    in the West Indies"</title> -- She<lb/>                    
                </p>
                <pb n="2" facs="Edgeworth_NLS_42180_1835_06_14_page02.jpg"/>
                <p>
                    has collected from long residence<lb/>
                    in Trinidad &amp; <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#St-Vincent_VC">St. Vincent</placeName><lb/>
                    <del>collected</del> materials which<lb/>
                    she purposes working up into<lb/>
                    a book for young people which<lb/>
                    will have the two great &amp;<lb/>
                    rarely united advantages<lb/>
                    which children (&amp; I believe<lb/>
                    parents most desire) <del>of</del><lb/>
                    It will be both <hi rend="underline">new</hi> &amp; <hi rend="underline">true</hi> -<lb/>
                </p>
                <p>
                    "Tell me a <hi rend="underline">new</hi> story <choice><orig>Mam<lb/>
                    <hi rend="underline">ma</hi></orig><reg>Mama</reg></choice> &amp; tell me a true story" - are<lb/>
                    the most frequent requests<lb/>
                    from young people - You or<lb/>
                    your son if I am not <choice><orig>mista<lb/>
                    ken</orig><reg>mistaken</reg></choice> are now engaged in<lb/>
                    the line of publishing for<lb/>
                    young people - <persName ref="./Personography.xml#CarmA1">M<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi>. Carmichael</persName><lb/>
                    is ambitious of being published<lb/>
                    by you - and I have promised<lb/>
                    to obtain an answer from<lb/>
                    you whether you wish to <choice><orig>en-<lb/>
                    gage</orig><reg>engage</reg></choice> with her or not - which<lb/>
                </p>
                <pb n="3" facs="Edgeworth_NLS_42180_1835_06_14_page03.jpg"/>
                <p>
                    answer must be given before<lb/>
                    the 20<hi rend="superscript">h</hi> of this month - for<lb/>
                    reasons which I need not <choice><orig>ex=<lb/>
                    plain</orig><reg>explain</reg></choice> to you - She would be<lb/>
                    glad to know whether you<lb/>
                    would rather have a book of<lb/>
                    the size of <title ref="./Workography.xml#Berth1">Bertha</title> in one volume<lb/>
                    or in 3<lb/>
                </p>
                <p>
                    Perhaps it might be best<lb/>
                    to begin with one volume &amp; try<lb/>
                    how that takes - <persName ref="./Personography.xml#LockJ1">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Lockhart</persName><lb/>
                    will convey this note to you<lb/>
                    and you will be so good to<lb/>
                    <del>convey</del> give your answer to<lb/>
                    him - who will make<lb/>
                    no delay in transmitting<lb/>
                    it to D<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> <unclear>Sir</unclear><lb/></p>
                    <closer>
                    Your <choice><orig>Obed<hi rend="superscript">t</hi></orig><reg>Obedient</reg></choice> Servant<lb/>
                    <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeM1">Maria Edgeworth</persName><lb/>
                    </closer>
             </div>
